              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Absolute intensities of 69 and 31 (gammas/100 neutron",
                " captures) of 4.946 and 3.684 MeV gammas, respectively,",
                " from 12C(n,gamma)13C used for normalization.",
                "Energy calibrated using annihilation radiation at",
                " 511.006(2) keV, 12C(n,gamma)13C line at 4946.0(10)",
                " keV, and 14N(n,gamma)15N line at 10830.0(10) keV.",
                "Intensity calibrated using relative efficiency of",
                " Ge(Li) detector crystal obtained as a function of",
                " gamma-ray energy using:",
                " 1) small irradiated sample of 179Hf for very low",
                "   energy end of the spectrum,",
                " 2) 113Cd(n,gamma)114Cd reaction for determining",
                "   full-energy-peak efficiency curve in the region",
                "   0.558-1.660 MeV by comparing with measurements from",
                "   bent-crystal spectrometer at ANL.",
                "60Co radioactive source and gamma rays from beryllium,",
                " nitrogen, and carbon sources employed to obtain",
                " double-escape efficiency curve."
              ]
            }
          ],
